 leads\nto an uncertainty of about 50% in estimates of the IGM density. Previous\nconclusions drawn using these sources, indicating that galaxy groups contain\nsignificant reservoirs of baryons in their IGM, are still valid when\nconsidering this level of uncertainty. In addition, we model the X-ray emission\nexpected from bent-double radio sources. We find that known sources in\nreasonably dense environments should be detectable in ~100 ks Chandra\nobservations. X-ray observations of these sources would place constraints on\nthe IGM density and AGN velocity that are complementary to radio observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Oct 2012 23:20:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Feb 2013 23:53:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
